## What Did NOT Work (and why)

- **tmux pane exhaustion** — Multiple times agents couldn't spawn because tmux panes were full. Fixed by killing stale panes (`tmux kill-pane -t %N`). Need to clean up more aggressively between stages.
- **TeamDelete race condition** — Agents sometimes didn't shut down fast enough for TeamDelete. Fixed with `rm -rf ~/.claude/teams/{name}` fallback, but this triggers sensitive file permission popup.
- **Sensitive file permission popups** — `.claude/teams/` directory is system-protected. `rm -rf` on it triggers approval popup. Can't be auto-approved via settings. Solution: use TeamDelete tool instead of rm -rf, wait for shutdown before deleting.
- **tech-writer agent stalled** — Stage 7 tech-writer agent appeared stuck (no output after 20+ minutes). Orchestrator took over and wrote readiness report directly. tech-writer eventually produced output that overwrote the file.
- **Analyst not sending [Fixes Applied]** — Multiple times analyst completed fixes but forgot to notify critics. Required manual nudging from orchestrator.
- **john delayed feedback** — john critic was sometimes slow to send feedback, requiring orchestrator nudges.

